properties.name: Jiu Zhai Gou
properties.description: Jiu Zhai Gou (九寨沟; literally "Valley of Nine Fortified Villages") is a national park and nature reserve on the edge of the Tibetan plateau; its elevation ranges from 2,000 to 4,500 meters. The park is known for its many multi-level waterfalls, colorful lakes, musical rapids and snow-capped peaks. The park is also home to a number of endangered plant and animal species, including the giant panda and rare orchids.
